The paper discusses the limitations of Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs) and the need for more biologically inspired approaches to Artificial Intelligence (AI) design. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the importance of investigating natural intelligence and replicating it in artificial cognitive architectures, which could fall under the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The paper also discusses the lack of theoretical underpinning in ANNs, which could relate to the cs.LG (Learning) sub-category. The mention of the strange state of affairs in contemporary AI R&D could suggest a connection to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the need for more suitable forms of natural intelligence for investigation, which could relate to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
